[[File:Beliadarzu.jpg|thumb|250px|Belia Darzu]]
'''Dark side marauder''' was a term used to describe [[warrior]]s who channeled the [[Force power/Legends|power]] of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to satisfy their violent desires, consequently driving them down the path of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. These individuals supplemented their battle prowess through a typically, but not exclusively, self-trained [[Force-sensitive/Legends|affinity]] with the Force, forging a [[Dark Jedi/Legends|dark amalgamation]] of a [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] and a [[Jedi Guardian/Legends|Jedi Guardian]]. Since the era of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]], dark side marauders arose from a wide variety of backgrounds. The majority pursued their [[Blood/Legends|bloody]] activities independently, though some were known to operate within major [[Galaxy/Legends|galactic]] factions, particularly the [[Sith/Legends|Sith Order]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Their chosen armaments were equally diverse, including [[Vibro-weapon/Legends|vibroweapons]], [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]], [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]], or simply the raw destructive potential of the dark side.

==Description==
The term dark side marauder applied to [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] beings who—due to their violent lifestyles, personalities or instincts—succumbed to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] while using [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to supplement their martial prowess. These [[warrior]]s combined the optimal traits of a [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] and the combat-focused [[Jedi Guardian/Legends|Guardians]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]—without the strict disciplines and [[Jedi Code/Legends|codes]] of the latter, they went on to become living weapons and extensions of the dark side as a result. Due to their typically [[Blood/Legends|bloodthirsty]] nature, dark side marauders often sought out activities allowing them to unleash their [[Force power/Legends|powers]] against other beings. To this end, many of these individuals undertook [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]]-like professions, with some becoming professional soldiers, [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguards]], enforcers or [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiators]]. Others simply acted as street thugs or adventurers.<ref name="DSSB">''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]''</ref>

Lacking a traditional set of customs, dark side marauders utilized a wide variety of combat techniques and armaments, including primitive [[Melee weapon/Legends|melee weapons]], [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] [[Blaster pistol/Legends|pistols]], [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifles]], [[Vibro-weapon/Legends|vibroweapons]], and even [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]]<ref name="DSSB" />—particularly the [[Double-bladed lightsaber/Legends|double-bladed variant]].<ref name="TJP">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref> A mere fraction possessed formal training in the ways of the Force, sometimes at the hands of a sadistic taskmaster, or alternatively from an exclusive [[Force Adept|Force-using]] organization. Some fell to the dark side through unintentional means, particularly from the trauma induced by their experiences in war or a committed crime. The majority developed their abilities at first hand while pursuing their lives of bloody conflict, often driven by the intoxicating influence of the dark side. As they gained more experience, marauders were known to eschew conventional weapons in favor of the dark side's pure destructive potential.<ref name="DSSB" />

==History==
[[File:DarkSideMarauderCard.jpg|thumb|left|150px|A dark side marauder wielding a lightsaber.]]
Since the days of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]], dark side marauders tended to operate independently rather than banding together, making them a somewhat uncommon sight throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. A portion of these individuals rose to prominence as [[Warlord/Legends|warlords]], establishing personal kingdoms and [[Fortress/Legends|strongholds]] during their violent conquests. In the time of the [[Old Sith Wars]], a contingent of [[Massassi/Legends|Massassi]] warriors—a [[Subspecies/Legends|sub-sect]] of the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith species]]—were [[Slavery/Legends|enslaved]] and [[Sith alchemy/Legends|alchemically]] [[Mutant|mutated]] by a [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] known as [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]], placing them under the brand of a dark side marauder.<ref name="DSSB" />

A number of dark side marauders achieved infamy during the [[New Sith Wars]],<ref name="DSSB" /> particularly [[Belia Darzu]],<ref name="JCF-DSSB">{{JCFCite|url=posts/24350750|board=Literature|thread=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties|user=Halagad_Ventor|date=2006-07-11|time=5:15 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801163409/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/evil-never-dies-the-sith-dynasties.24202765/page-14}}</ref> a leading figure of the [[New Sith|resurgent Sith faction]].<ref name="END">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref> Additionally, by the time of the [[Ruusan campaign]], a powerful [[Sith Warrior]] known as [[Kaox Krul]] battled against the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] as a servant of the [[Brotherhood of Darkness/Legends|Brotherhood of Darkness]]. The dark side marauders maintained a consistent presence in the subsequent waning [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the Galactic Republic. Their violent exploits frequently provoked the intervention of the Jedi, resulting in the swift annihilation of the marauders' domains. Another marauder who followed the Sith teachings included [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], a Sith Lord who—under the [[Sith apprentice/Legends|apprenticeship]] of [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]]—was forged into a ruthless living weapon. At least one marauder emerged from the ranks of the Jedi Order, most notably the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|failed]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Xanatos]].<ref name="DSSB" />

With the eventual fall of the Republic and the Jedi, several dark side marauders operated within the newly-established [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. [[Standard month/Legends|Months]] after the beginning of the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Jedi Purge]], a sadistic Force Adept called [[Del Korrot]] worked as a [[Jedi hunter/Legends|Jedi hunter]] on behalf of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine himself. Another individual named [[Azrakel]] was initially a subject of Palpatine's dark side experiments, though he was later mentored into a hate-filled minion of [[Supreme Prophet]] [[Kadann]].<ref name="DSSB" /> Two additional marauders, [[Gorc]] and [[Picaroon C. Boodle|Pic]], were alchemically mutated by the Imperial [[Scientist/Legends|scientist]] known as [[Cronal]], forging a symbiotic [[Force-bond/Legends|bond]] between the pair.<ref name="Wiz-DFS">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050609a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 5: Two Peas in a Pod}}</ref> By the end of the Jedi Purge, a powerful darksider called [[Arden Lyn]]—who once lived during the [[First Great Schism]]—awoke from a multi-[[Millennium/Legends|millennia]]-long [[Sleep/Legends|slumber]], eventually entering the service of Palpatine as an [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]].<ref name="TEP">{{GamerCite|5|The Emperor's Pawns}}</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], servants of Emperor Palpatine were known to seek out independent dark side marauders, aiming to either recruit these warriors or eliminate them as threats to the Imperial cause. In particular, the Force-attuned mercenary named [[Sedriss QL|Sedriss]] ultimately became one of Palpatine's [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adepts]]. The marauders experienced a period of resurgence after the Empire's [[Imperial Remnant|downfall]], an event which led to the rise of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the emergence of the [[New Jedi Order|New Jedi]], and the cataclysmic [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. This tumultuous era gave the marauders an opportunity to expand their activities unchecked and unopposed, sparking a new golden age for their kind.<ref name="DSSB" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:DarkSideEnforcerCard.jpg|thumb|right|150px|The Dark Side Enforcer figurine card, resembling the original dark side marauder.]]
The dark side marauder (alternatively stylized as Dark Side Marauder) is a prestige character class from the [[Wizards of the Coast]] edition of the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''. Details regarding the mechanics of the class, as well as some [[in-universe]] backstory, were provided in ''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]'', a [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] supplement published in [[2001]].<ref name="DSSB" /> The ''[[Star Wars Miniatures]]'' set named [[Champions of the Force (Star Wars Miniatures)|''Champions of the Force'']] contains a figurine—labeled the "Dark Side Enforcer"—resembling the original dark side marauder depicted in ''The Dark Side Sourcebook''.<ref name="COTF">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/championsgallery|text=''Champions of the Force'' Gallery}}</ref>

